data.name: bulbasaur
data.description: For some time after its birth, it grows by gaining nourishment from the seed on its back.

data.name: ivysaur
data.description: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flowers coming bloom.

data.name: venusaur
data.description: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokemon.

data.name: charmander
data.description: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.

data.name: charmeleon
data.description: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.

data.name: charizard
data.description: It is said that Charizards fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.

data.name: squirtle
data.description: It shelters itself in its shell then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.

data.name: wartortle
data.description: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.

data.name: blastoise
data.description: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.

data.name: caterpie
data.description: It releases a stench from its red antenna to repel enemies. It grows by molting repeatedly.

data.name: metapod
data.description: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.

data.name: butterfree
data.description: It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

data.name: weedle
data.description: It eats its weight in leaves every day. It fends off attackers with the needle on its head.

data.name: kakuna
data.description: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

data.name: beedrill
data.description: Its best attack involves flying around at high speed, striking with poison needles, then flying off.

data.name: pidgey
data.description: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

data.name: pidgeotto
data.description: It flies over its wide territory in search of prey, downing it with its highly developed claws.

data.name: pidgeot
data.description: It flies over its wide territory in search of prey, downing it with its highly developed claws.

data.name: rattata
data.description: It searches for food all day. It gnaws on hard objects to wear down its fangs, which grow constantly during its lifetime.

data.name: raticate
data.description: With its long fangs, this surprisingly violent Pokemon can gnaw away even thick concrete with ease.

data.name: spearow
data.description: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.

data.name: fearow
data.description: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.

data.name: ekans
data.description: It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind.

data.name: arbok
data.description: The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes while they are frozen in fear.

data.name: pikachu
data.description: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.

data.name: raichu
data.description: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

data.name: sandshrew
data.description: It digs deep burrows to live in. When in danger, it rolls up its body to withstand attacks.

data.name: sandslash
data.description: The spikes on its body are made up of its hardened hide. It rolls up and attacks foes with its spikes.

data.name: nidoran-f
data.description: While it does not prefer to fight, even one drop of the poison it secretes from barbs can be fatal.

data.name: nidorina
data.description: When it senses danger, it raises all the barbs on its body. These barbs grow slower than Nidorinos.

data.name: nidoqueen
data.description: Its entire body is armored with hard scales. It will protect the young in its burrow with its life.

data.name: nidoran-m
data.description: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.

data.name: nidorino
data.description: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes poison upon impact.

data.name: nidoking
data.description: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.

data.name: clefairy
data.description: On nights with a full moon, Clefairy gather from all over and dance. Bathing in moonlight makes them float.

data.name: clefable
data.description: Their ears are sensitive enough to hear a pin drop from over a mile away, so theyre usually found in quiet places.

data.name: vulpix
data.description: As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.

data.name: ninetales
data.description: Each of its nine tails is imbued with supernatural power, and it can live for a thousand years.

data.name: jigglypuff
data.description: Looking into its cute, round eyes makes it start singing a song so pleasant listeners cant help but fall asleep.

data.name: wigglytuff
data.description: Its fine fur feels so pleasant, those who accidentally touch it cannot take their hands away.

data.name: zubat
data.description: It does not need eyes, because it emits ultrasonic waves to check its surroundings while it flies.

data.name: golbat
data.description: Flitting around in the dead of night, it sinks its fangs into its prey and drains a nearly fatal amount of blood.

data.name: oddish
data.description: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.

data.name: gloom
data.description: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

data.name: vileplume
data.description: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.

data.name: paras
data.description: Mushrooms named tochukaso grow on its back. They grow along with the host Paras.

data.name: parasect
data.description: A mushroom grown larger than the hosts body controls Parasect. It scatters poisonous spores.

data.name: venonat
data.description: Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At night, its kind is drawn by light.

data.name: venomoth
data.description: It flutters its wings to scatter dustlike scales. The scales leach toxins if they contact skin.

data.name: diglett
data.description: A Pokemon that lives underground. Because of its dark habitat, it is repelled by bright sunlight.

data.name: dugtrio
data.description: Its three heads move alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles.

data.name: meowth
data.description: It is nocturnal in nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter brightly.

data.name: persian
data.description: A very haughty Pokemon. Among fans, the size of the jewel in its forehead is a topic of much talk.

data.name: psyduck
data.description: When headaches stimulate its brain cells, which are usually inactive, it can use a mysterious power.

data.name: golduck
data.description: When its forehead shines mysteriously, Golduck can use the full extent of its power.

data.name: mankey
data.description: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.

data.name: primeape
data.description: It grows angry if you see its eyes and gets angrier if you run. If you beat it, it gets even madder.

data.name: growlithe
data.description: Extremely loyal to its Trainer, it will bark at those who approach the Trainer unexpectedly and run them out of town.

data.name: arcanine
data.description: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.

data.name: poliwag
data.description: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.

data.name: poliwhirl
data.description: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.

data.name: poliwrath
data.description: With its extremely tough muscles, it can keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.

data.name: abra
data.description: Using its psychic power is such a strain on its brain that it needs to sleep for 18 hours a day.

data.name: kadabra
data.description: It stares at its silver spoon to focus its mind. It emits more alpha waves while doing so.

data.name: alakazam
data.description: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.

data.name: machop
data.description: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.

data.name: machoke
data.description: It happily carries heavy cargo to toughen up. It willingly does hard work for people.

data.name: machamp
data.description: Its four muscled arms slam foes with powerful punches and chops at blinding speed.

data.name: bellsprout
data.description: It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.

data.name: weepinbell
data.description: A Pokemon that appears to be a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.

data.name: victreebel
data.description: It pools in its mouth a fluid with a honey-like scent, which is really an acid that dissolves anything.

data.name: tentacool
data.description: Because its body is almost entirely composed of water, it shrivels up if it is washed ashore.

data.name: tentacruel
data.description: It extends its 80 tentacles to form an encircling poisonous net that is difficult to escape.

data.name: geodude
data.description: At rest, it looks just like a rock. Carelessly stepping on it will make it swing its fists angrily.

data.name: graveler
data.description: It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pokemon can stop it without difficulty.

data.name: golem
data.description: Even dynamite cant harm its hard, boulder-like body. It sheds its hide just once a year.

data.name: ponyta
data.description: As a newborn, it can barely stand. However, through galloping, its legs are made tougher and faster.

data.name: rapidash
data.description: When at an all-out gallop, its blazing mane sparkles, enhancing its beautiful appearance.

data.name: slowpoke
data.description: Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.

data.name: slowbro
data.description: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.

data.name: magnemite
data.description: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

data.name: magneton
data.description: The stronger electromagnetic waves from the three linked Magnemite are enough to dry out surrounding moisture.

data.name: farfetchd
data.description: It cant live without the stalk it holds. Thats why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

data.name: doduo
data.description: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.

data.name: dodrio
data.description: When Doduo evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. It runs at nearly 40 mph.

data.name: seel
data.description: The colder it gets, the better it feels. It joyfully swims around oceans so cold that they are filled with floating ice.

data.name: dewgong
data.description: Its streamlined body has low resistance, and it swims around cold oceans at a speed of eight knots.

data.name: grimer
data.description: Born from sludge, these Pokemon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

data.name: muk
data.description: Its so stinky! Muks body contains toxic elements, and any plant will wilt when it passes by.

data.name: shellder
data.description: It swims backward by opening and closing its two shells. Its large tongue is always kept hanging out.

data.name: cloyster
data.description: It fights by keeping its shell tightly shut for protection and by shooting spikes to repel foes.

data.name: gastly
data.description: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

data.name: haunter
data.description: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

data.name: gengar
data.description: The leer that floats in darkness belongs to a Gengar delighting in casting curses on people.

data.name: onix
data.description: Opening its large mouth, it ingests massive amounts of soil and creates long tunnels.

data.name: drowzee
data.description: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.

data.name: hypno
data.description: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even in someone who just woke up.

data.name: krabby
data.description: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are broken in battle.

data.name: kingler
data.description: The larger pincer has 10,000- horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.

data.name: voltorb
data.description: It looks just like a Pok Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on contact.

data.name: electrode
data.description: It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.

data.name: exeggcute
data.description: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.

data.name: exeggutor
data.description: It is called The Walking Jungle. If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

data.name: cubone
data.description: When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.

data.name: marowak
data.description: From its birth, this savage Pokemon constantly holds bones. It is skilled in using them as weapons.

data.name: hitmonlee
data.description: Its legs can stretch double. First-time foes are startled by its extensible reach.

data.name: hitmonchan
data.description: The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.

data.name: lickitung
data.description: Being licked by its long, saliva-covered tongue leaves a tingling sensation. Extending its tongue retracts its tail.

data.name: koffing
data.description: Toxic gas is held within its thin, balloon-shaped body, so it can cause massive explosions.

data.name: weezing
data.description: Inhaling toxic fumes from trash and mixing them inside its body lets it spread an even fouler stench.

data.name: rhyhorn
data.description: Its powerful tackles can destroy anything. However, it is too slow witted to help people work.

data.name: rhydon
data.description: Standing on its hind legs freed its forelegs and made it smarter. It is very forgetful, however.

data.name: chansey
data.description: A kindly Pokemon that lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokmon or people.

data.name: tangela
data.description: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.

data.name: kangaskhan
data.description: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.

data.name: horsea
data.description: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

data.name: seadra
data.description: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional-medicine ingredients.

data.name: goldeen
data.description: Though it appears very elegant when swimming with fins unfurled, it can jab powerfully with its horn.

data.name: seaking
data.description: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

data.name: staryu
data.description: As long as its red core remains, it can regenerate its body instantly, even if its torn apart.

data.name: starmie
data.description: Its core shines in many colors and sends radio signals into space to communicate with something.

data.name: mr-mime
data.description: It shapes an invisible wall in midair by minutely vibrating its fingertips to stop molecules in the air.

data.name: scyther
data.description: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.

data.name: jynx
data.description: Its cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.

data.name: electabuzz
data.description: Research is progressing on storing lightning in Electabuzz so this energy can be used at any time.

data.name: magmar
data.description: The scorching fire exhaled by Magmar forms heat waves around its body, making it hard to see the Pokemon clearly.

data.name: pinsir
data.description: It grips prey with its powerful pincers and will not let go until the prey is torn in half.

data.name: tauros
data.description: Once it takes aim at its foe, it makes a headlong charge. It is famous for its violent nature.

data.name: magikarp
data.description: A Magikarp living for many years can leap a mountain using Splash. The move remains useless, though.

data.name: gyarados
data.description: Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.

data.name: lapras
data.description: Able to understand human speech and very intelligent, it loves to swim in the sea with people on its back.

data.name: ditto
data.description: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.

data.name: eevee
data.description: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokemon conceals many different possible evolutions.

data.name: vaporeon
data.description: Its cell composition is similar to water molecules. As a result, it cant be seen when it melts away into water.

data.name: jolteon
data.description: By storing electricity in its body, it can shoot its bristlelike fur like a barrage of missiles.

data.name: flareon
data.description: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees F.

data.name: porygon
data.description: A man-made Pokemon created using advanced scientific means. It can move freely in cyberspace.

data.name: omanyte
data.description: A Pokemon that was resurrected from a fossil using modern science. It swam in ancient seas.

data.name: omastar
data.description: It is thought that this Pokemon became extinct because its spiral shell grew too large.

data.name: kabuto
data.description: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a stiff shell.

data.name: kabutops
data.description: It is thought that this Pokemon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.

data.name: aerodactyl
data.description: A Pokemon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.

data.name: snorlax
data.description: When its belly is full, it becomes too lethargic to even lift a finger, so it is safe to bounce on its belly.

data.name: articuno
data.description: A legendary bird Pokemon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

data.name: zapdos
data.description: A legendary Pokemon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

data.name: moltres
data.description: One of the legendary bird Pokemon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

data.name: dratini
data.description: It is called the Mirage Pokemon because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.

data.name: dragonair
data.description: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.

data.name: dragonite
data.description: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

data.name: mewtwo
data.description: A Pokemon created by recombining Mews genes. Its said to have the most savage heart among Pokmon.

data.name: mew
data.description: Mew is said to possess the genetic composition of all Pokemon. It is capable of making itself invisible at will, so it entirely avoids notice even if it approaches people.
